en_8502334_0	Fidel Ángel Castro Díaz-Balart was found on Thursday morning and is said to have suffered from depression.
en_8502334_1	The first-born son of the late president was nicknamed “Fidelito”, or Little Fidel, because of the family resemblance.
en_8502334_2	He was a nuclear physicist, trained by the former Soviet Union.
en_8502334_3	“Fidel Castro Díaz-Balart, who had been treated by a group of doctors for several months due to deep depression, took his life this morning,” Cuba’s official newspaper Granma reported.
en_8502334_4	State television said he had been receiving medical treatment as an outpatient in recent months, following a hospital stay.
en_8502334_5	At the time of his death, he was a scientific adviser for the Cuban Council of State and he served as vice president of Cuba’s Academy of Sciences.
en_8502334_6	He headed the island’s nuclear programme from 1980 to 1992, before it was suspended after the Soviet Union’s collapse.
en_8502334_7	His maternal family went on to become prominent figures in the anti-Castro community in Florida.
en_8502334_8	His cousin Mario Díaz-Balart is a US congressman.
en_8502334_9	His father, Fidel Castro, a revolutionary figure and one of the world’s longest serving political leaders, died aged 90 in 2016.
en_8502334_10	Courtesy: BBC
